{When things move so quickly as it is the case with Blitz games, controlling
all the factors involved in the final results is a bit of an utopia. And yet,
when you lose one game and then another, something must be done, something
must change to save you from disaster. Luckily, Kenny trained his physical
srength before the competition, so he could run upstairs, change his shirt and
be in time for his next game. Guess what, it worked! He won a very important
R4, Day 2 Blitz game against the GM from Tanta.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7
4. e4 d6 5. h3 O-O 6. Be3 c5 7. d5 e6 8. Nf3 exd5 9. exd5 Re8 10. Bd3 Bh6 11.
